Ad Text:
A role with real purpose.

You‚Äôve worked on complex technology programs where the detail genuinely mattered. You‚Äôve untangled integrations, mapped data flows across systems that don‚Äôt naturally talk to each other, and asked the questions that prevent delivery issues from surfacing too late.

But you may be craving more meaning from the work itself.

This role sits at the intersection of technology and humanity. The platforms you help shape will support Australians at some of the most vulnerable moments of their lives, when they are seeking information, guidance, and reassurance following a cancer diagnosis.

Here, business analysis is not an abstract exercise. Your work directly influences how quickly someone reaches the right support, how seamlessly services connect across states, and how equitably care is delivered nationwide.

That‚Äôs what makes this role different, and why experienced Business Analysts choose to move now.

About the role

Reporting to the Stream Delivery Lead ‚Äì Customer Experience, you will play a critical role in the National Cancer Navigation Service Program, a major national initiative transforming how people affected by cancer access information and support.

You will be responsible for eliciting, analysing, and documenting detailed business, functional, and data requirements across CRM, contact centre, and integration platforms. The environment is complex and federated, spanning multiple states, existing CRM platforms, and diverse stakeholder groups.

Working closely with the Product Owner ‚Äì Customer Experience, Product Manager, architects, vendors, and state-based teams, you will act as a trusted bridge between service design, human need, and technical delivery.

This is a Fixed Term Contract until the end of June 2027, aligned to a pivotal discovery and delivery phase of the program.

What you‚Äôll lead / do

Elicit and document functional and non-functional requirements, workflows, and business rules across CRM, contact centre and integration platforms
Analyse and document complex data mappings and data flows across multiple state CRM environments
Work closely with vendors and technical teams to translate requirements into clear, testable acceptance criteria
Support discovery and detailed analysis for major upcoming releases, including CRM integration and telephony
Document system integration and user acceptance test cases, and support business users through UAT
Engage sensitively with state-based stakeholders, respecting existing systems, investments, and local context
Operate within an agile delivery environment, applying just-enough documentation and iterative practices
Contribute to a collaborative, psychologically safe program culture grounded in empathy and professionalism

ÔªøWhat you‚Äôll bring

5+ years‚Äô experience as a Senior Business Analyst on complex, customer-facing technology programs
Proven experience across CRM platforms, ideally Microsoft Dynamics 365, with Salesforce exposure highly regarded
Practical understanding of system integration, data synchronisation, and data quality challenges
Experience working across contact centre platforms and multi-vendor delivery environments
Confidence operating in federated or matrixed organisations with complex stakeholder landscapes
High emotional intelligence, strong listening skills, and the ability to read a room
A pragmatic, collaborative mindset, willing to step beyond strict role boundaries to help the program succeed
A genuine alignment to purpose and motivation to use technology for social impact

About Cancer Council and the Program

Cancer Council is Australia‚Äôs leading cancer charity, a trusted voice, advocate, and lifeline for millions.

The Australian Cancer Nursing and Navigation Program (ACNNP) aims to connect people with cancer to quality care, information, and support services, no matter their cancer type, background, or location.

As part of the ACNNP, Cancer Council will be delivering the National Cancer Navigation Service, enhancing and expanding our cancer information and support service through the creation of a new national cancer navigation service, offering new ways for more people affected by cancer to access support and information that best meets their needs, now and into the future.

This Customer Experience stream will deliver an integrated CRM, contact-centre, and data ecosystem that connects patients, carers, and clinicians to the right support, wherever they are in their cancer journey. We're looking for a highly skilled and experienced Senior SAP Functional Analyst to join our dynamic IT team at our Daikin Park in Warwick Farm, NSW. In this role, you will analyse the business problems and requirements to design a fully functional solution, assisting the Enterprise Architect to evaluate and finalise the SAP solutions. Your key responsibilities will include:


SAP System Expertise & Support: Leading the entire lifecycle of SAP Supply Chain Management (SCM) module (including WM, MM, PP) implementation and optimisation. Business Process Analysis and Optimisation: Focuses on optimising supply chain management processes by analysing current operations and recommending improvements. You'll collaborate closely with business users to gather and document their requirements, then map these needs to existing or new SAP functionalities. Problem Resolution & Optimisation: Act as a key resource for troubleshooting and resolving critical SAP incidents and problems. You'll perform root cause analysis, implement corrective actions, and proactively identify areas for system optimisation to enhance performance and user experience.

Project Leadership & Collaboration: Play a vital role in SAP-related projects, including upgrades, migrations, and new module implementations. You'll work seamlessly with other IT teams (e.g., Basis, ABAP developers), external consultants, and business users to deliver successful outcomes.




We're looking for someone who brings:

You're a highly experienced and technically proficient SAP professional with a deep understanding of supply chain processes and a passion for optimizing systems. You're a natural problem-solver, an excellent communicator, and thrive in a dynamic, multicultural environment.

We're looking for someone who brings:

Higher education in Computer Sciences / Any Engineering Studies, and related SAP certification is mandatory.

Minimum of 10 years of hands-on/proven experience in SAP SCM functional roles covering Materials Management (MM), Production Planning (PP), Sales and Distribution (SD), and Warehouse Management (WM).

Proven experience in full life-cycle SAP implementations, including gathering requirements, configuring systems, conducting testing, and supporting go-live.

Experience in S/4HANA System conversion is a must.

Proficient and strong understanding of supply chain processes such as procurement, inventory management, production planning, and order fulfilment.

Knowledge of SQL and PL/SQL, with experience in Manhattan Scale highly preferred.


Ability to write functional specifications for custom developments and support ABAP teams as needed.

Experience with SAP interfaces, integrations, and EDI (Electronic Data Interchange) with Manhattan Scale is beneficial.

Ad Text:

Here at Snack Brands Australia, we proudly make some of Australia‚Äôs favourite snacks including Kettle, CC‚Äôs, Thins, Cheezels, The Natural Chip Company and Nice & Natural. We encourage a culture that is exciting, challenging and we strive for innovation in everything we do. Our aim is for our people to share in our success, enjoy our products and reap the benefits of their hard work within a supportive environment where work life balance is encouraged!


About the role:


We‚Äôre looking for an experienced Snr Functional & Technical Analyst D365 SCO to join our IT Applications team and drive the successful delivery of D365 projects, enhancements and support across our Operations function.

This role will be based between our head office in Norwest with regular travel to our manufacturing site at Orchard Hills.

What you‚Äôll be responsible for:


Leading the transition from legacy systems to Dynamics 365 F&O Supply Chain modules, performing fit-gap analyses and configuring modules to meet specific business workflows..
Conduct workshops with stakeholders to define business requirements.
Develop critical project artifacts, including Business Requirement Specifications (BRS), Functional Design Documents (FDD), technical requirements and process flows.
Reduce the Production and Logistic reliance on legacy solutions by migrating to Dynamics 365 Operations functionality.
Conduct Dynamics F&O working sessions to demonstrate system capabilities by configuring core modules, data migration and reporting to enable workflows that meet business requirements.
Partner with Finance, Production, and Logistics teams to ensure seamless and optimised end-to-end data flow and reporting.
Support supply chain and manufacturing users including production problems, incidents and change requests i.e. manage and resolve open tickets in your support queue.
Follow ITIL processes and methodologies for approval and migration of changes to production
Collaborate with Operations, Project Office and IT teams to resolve issues across operations, manufacturing, warehousing, distribution and inventory.
Partner with supply chain and operations departments across the business to ensure solutions meet operational requirements and align with business milestones.
Coordinate project plans, budgets and reporting.
Influence best practice solution architecture and support a high-performance IT culture.
Work with vendors to provide support and upgrade information.
Develop, execute and lead unit, system and user testing as required to implement changes into production
Build strong relationships across stakeholders and business users.¬†

What you‚Äôll bring to the role:
Proven experience as a Senior Functional and Technical analyst in Dynamics F&O Supply Chain modules.
Experience in FMCG processes including order management, demand and supply planning, MRP, manufacturing, warehouse management, inventory management, procurement.
Excellent Dynamics 365 and business process knowledge in Supply Chain modules.
Solution knowledge of Dynamics 365, SQL data base and integration technologies.
Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement and influencing skills.
Strong analytical, project planning and commercial acumen.
Ability to manage multiple initiatives, navigate conflicting priorities and work with senior leaders¬†


What can you expect in return?
A supportive working environment (with plenty of snacks on hand!) where you'll feel engaged and valued, career growth, Birthday Leave, Access to discounts on Retailers, onsite parking (including electric car charging stations) and a focus on health and wellness (like Wellbeing Days!) to make your workplace more enjoyable!
